In his first address to the U.N. General Assembly, President Donald Trump called for nations to work together to confront threats from rogue regimes like North Korea and Iran. He emphasized the importance of strong and independent nations that embrace their sovereignty to promote security, prosperity, and peace. Trump condemned North Korea's development of nuclear weapons and warned that the United States would completely destroy the country if forced to defend itself or its allies. He also criticized Iran for its destabilizing activities and called on the world to join together to end pursuits of death and destruction. Trump urged all responsible nations to isolate these regimes until they stop their hostility. The President emphasized the importance of sovereignty and noted that America is an example of success when a people take responsibility for their future. He encouraged all Member States to renew their commitment to their people, global peace, and prosperity.